title: Re-appointments to the Hospital Authority
content_text:
p>
    The Government announced today (March 26) the re-appointment of two serving 
    members to the Hospital Authority for a two-year term with effect from April 
    1, 2010. The two members are Ms Lau Ka-shi and Mr David Lie-A-Cheong Tai-chong. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, thanked the two members for 
    their advice and contributions to the Hospital Authority in the past term. With effect from April 1, 2010, the Hospital Authority comprises a chairman,

21 non-official members, three public officers and one principal officer from the Hospital Authority. The membership list is as follows: Chairman:
